    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Then we entered a wood, not like the dark woods we have here&mdash;no, no; but light, and all over glorious; the branches of the trees moved to and fro, and we all cried out, &ldquo;We will dwell safely in the wilderness and sleep in the woods.&rdquo;<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">1<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"EW 17.1\" data-link=\"28.89\">Early Writings, 17, 18</span>.</span></a></sup>",
